children.subject: For what it's worth, teaching evaluations are available here: https://hkn.eecs.berkeley.edu/coursesurveys/course/CS/162

history.content: Kubi is a good lecturer (my only gripe with him is that he seems to assume that we know much more about computer systems than we actually do but overall, he is a good lecturer with a great sense of humor). The exams are also hard but straightforward. I honestly don't think professor matters for this class unless it's a professor renowned for their atrocious teaching style or bad grading distribution, just make sure you have a very strong project team since projects will take the bulk of your time in this class.

I see that the professor for CS 162 in the Fall is David Culler, who last taught the course Fall 2014, according to BerkeleyTime (probably before anyone on here took it ha), and that for Spring is John Kubiatowicz, who last taught it Fall 2015 (also probably before anyone took it). Does anyone know if professors matter for the course, and if so, which one I should go with (if you have taken any course with either professor)? FWIW I also don't have a group so I'm wondering if I should postpone it to the Spring, or even senior year when (hopefully) Stoica teaches it.

edit: I see Kubiatowicz is teaching it this semester, my bad. Anyone currently taking the class have opinions on his teaching?
